{
  "texts": [
    "Figure 3 shows a gaze-position signal with high (a) and low (d) sampling frequency.",
    "Note, in particular, the lack of samples during saccades in (d) compared to (a).",
    "When is a low sampling frequency of, say, 30 Hz sufficient?",
    "Atkins, Tien, Khan, Meneghetti, & Zheng (2013) argued that 30 Hz is enough to investigate what objects surgeons look at in an operating room.",
    "A 30-Hz sampling rate provides an estimate of where someone looks every 33.3 ms."
  ]
}